<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Source of lots of magical items (even stat potions once you go to level 25 and deeper). <p>
The Armor of the Sand Worm Queen is nice, but you need poison resistance to take on the Killer Queen. 
</p>
<p>
Genocide might not give you any items or XP, but may be necessary as this is a breeders-only dungeon! Stealth and/or speed help in preventing out-of-control masses, and can make the dungeon rather easy. The same goes double for area attacks, especially distance area attacks like Noxious Cloud. 
</p>
<p>
This is one of the easiest level to 'farm'. 'Farming' is a cheat where you let breeders fill a room and you use area effect spells to get lots of XP/items. (Sleazy players playing worshippers of certain gods can farm piety here as well.) Then you want for them to fill the room again...  Be careful, though, not to let breeders with breath attacks build up -- even if you are too strong for breaths to be a threat, they can destroy the more fragile treasure types (like potions... say, potions of stat!). 
</p>
<p>
The vaults in the Sandworm Lair are an excellent source of magic tomes, good potions (like Intelligence, Restore Mana, Healing/*Healing*, and the stronger cure-insanity variants), and good magic devices. A Melkor worshipper looking for medium-to-good rods to drain in the early midgame will find all s/he wants in the Sandworm Lair. Note that many vaults are brimming in traps -- don't just bring detection, bring a way of disarming traps too, as much of the best loot is buried among the durn things. 
</p>
<p>
If you're used to bringing empty bottles everywhere, you might want to save yourself the bother here -- most of the time you'll find yourself throwing the bottles away at the end of each visit, to haul out more loot. Heck, you might just be throwing away your book of beginner cantrips (if applicable) at the end of each visit. On the other hand, occasionally you'll find fountains of cure foo insanity or restore foo, so it's hard to say. 
</p>
<p>
With the Cthangband and other extra monsters on the Sandworm Lair becomes much more difficult. In particular, the Cthangband unique Shudde M'ell is worse than the Sandworm Queen. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


